The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for the paper screening phase of systematic literature reviews, which is a common practice in the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of statistical properties and algorithms, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of classification problems, which can be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and deep learning (cs.DL).
